                <!-- Card Content - Collapse -->
                <div class="collapse" id="revenueRecognitionCard">

                  <div class="card-body">
                    <b>Objective:</b>
                    <br>
                    To test that the client recognises revenue in terms of IFRS 15.						
                    <br><br>
                    <b>Audit Approach:</b>
                    <br>
                    - Enquire from the client the different types of revenue streams.
                    <br>
                    - Enquire from the client how each revenue stream is recognised.
                    <br>
                    - Determine if th client's recognition is in line with IFRS 15 by applying the points below to the revenue recognition criteria.
                    <br><br>

                    <div class="form-group">
                      <label><b>REVENUE - SYSTEM DESCRIPTION</b></label>
                      <textarea rows="6" class="form-control">

                      </textarea>
                    </div> 
                    
                    <div class="form-group">
                      <label><b>REVENUE - WALKTHROUGH</b></label>
                      <textarea rows="6" class="form-control">

                      </textarea>
                    </div>
                    
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
                   
            
              <!--Revenue Recognition Card-->
              <div class="card shadow mb-4">

                <!-- Card Header - Accordion -->
                <a href="#risksAtFSLCard" class="d-block card-header py-3" data-toggle="collapse" role="button" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseCardExample">
                    <h6 class="m-0 font-weight-bold text-primary">REVENUE FROM CONTRACTS WITH CUSTOMERS</h6>
                </a>

                <!-- Card Content - Collapse -->
                <div class="collapse" id="risksAtFSLCard">

                  <div class="card-body">
                    <div class="form-group">
                      <p>1. 
                        Identify the contract with a customer<br>
                        The following criteria are all required in order to qualify as a contract with a customer:<br>
                      </p>
                      <label><b>a) The contract has been approved by the parties </b></label>
                      <input class="form-control"/><br/>

                      <label><b>b) The entity can identify each party's rights regarding the goods or services to be delivered </b></label>
                      <input class="form-control"/><br/>

                      <label><b>c) The entity can identify the payment terms for the goods or services to be delivered</b></label>
                      <input class="form-control"/><br/>

                      <label><b>d) The contract has commercial substance </b></label>
                      <input class="form-control"/><br>

                      <label><b>e) It is probable that the entity will collect the consideration to which it is entitled in exchange for the delivery of goods or services. </b></label>
                      <input class="form-control"/>


                    </div><br>

                    <div class="form-group">
                      <p>2. Identify the performance obligation in the contract<br><br>
                      The performance obligaton need to be determined at contract inception, by identifying the distinct goods or services in the contract.<br><br>
                    For a good or service to be distinct it must satisfy both of the following conditions:</p><br>
                      <label><b>
                        a) The customer can benefit from the good or service either on its own or in combination with other resources available to the customer
                      </b></label>
                      <input class="form-control"/><br>

                      <label><b>
                        b) The entity's promise to transfer the good or service to the customer is separable from the other promises in the contract.
                      </b></label>
                      <input class="form-control"/><br>
                    </div>

                    <div class="form-group">
                      <label><b>3. Determine the transaction price:</b></label>
                      <input class="form-control"/>
                    </div>

                    <div class="form-group">
                      <label><b>4. Allocate the transaction price to separate performance obligations
                      </b></label>
                      <input class="form-control"/>
                    </div>

                    <div class="form-group">
                      <label><b>5. Recognise revenue as the entity satisfies a performance obligation<br>		
                        "An entity should recognise revenue as the performance obligations are satisfied.<br> 
                        A performance obligation is satisfied when control of the underlying goods or services is transferred to the customer."		<br>		
                        Control is defined as the ability to direct the use of and obtain substantially all of the remaining benefits from the asset underlying the good or service.			
                      </b></label>
                      <input class="form-control"/>
                    </div>

                    <br>
                      <p>Due to the nature of the revenue, discounting of revenue and the resulting cost of sales is immaterial and therefore no further assessment is required.</p>
                    <br><br> 
                  </div>
                </div>               
              </div>
              
